Inside the country, the same logic of hierarchy and exclusion shaped domestic policy. The administration threatened to revoke Temporary Protected Status for Ukrainians and ordered a review of the broader TPS program, putting about a million people from 17 countries in limbo. It issued an executive order to end federal benefits for undocumented immigrants and to penalize sanctuary jurisdictions. ICE leadership was reshuffled to increase deportations, and the Senate passed a budget resolution allocating $175 billion for border security and mass deportations. At the same time, House and administration budget plans extended tax cuts for the wealthy while mandating deep cuts to Medicaid, Social Security, Medicare, and food assistance programs. The message was that citizenship and security would be stratified by status, ideology, and wealth. Those deemed \'93illegal\'94 or insufficiently loyal would lose access to the safety net. Those with capital and connections would see their interests protected.\
